{"id": "test-03122", "text": "RUGBY UNION - CAMPESE SIGNS OFF WITH TRY IN WALLABY ROMP.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 11, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "RUGBY UNION"}, {"start": 14, "end": 21, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "CAMPESE"}, {"start": 44, "end": 51, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "WALLABY"}]}
{"id": "test-03123", "text": "LONDON 1996-12-07", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 6, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "LONDON"}]}
{"id": "test-03124", "text": "Australia bade farewell to David Campese in spectacular fashion by overwhelming the Barbarians 39-12 in the final match of their European tour at Twickenham on Saturday.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 9, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Australia"}, {"start": 27, "end": 40, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "David Campese"}, {"start": 84, "end": 94, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Barbarians"}, {"start": 129, "end": 137, "ent_type": "MISC", "text": "European"}, {"start": 146, "end": 156, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Twickenham"}]}
{"id": "test-03125", "text": "The Wallabies ran in five tries with Campese, who has retired from test rugby after collecting 101 caps and a world record 64 tries, adding one last touchdown in a Wallaby jersey before departing the international game.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 4, "end": 13, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Wallabies"}, {"start": 37, "end": 44, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Campese"}, {"start": 164, "end": 171, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Wallaby"}]}
{"id": "test-03126", "text": "The Barbarians included 14 internationals but, with only two pre-match practice sessions behind them, proved no real match for a Wallaby side determined to finish their 12-match tour unbeaten.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 4, "end": 14, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Barbarians"}, {"start": 129, "end": 136, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Wallaby"}]}
{"id": "test-03127", "text": "The touring team were 27-0 ahead by half-time before easing up in the second-half.", "gold_mentions": []}
{"id": "test-03128", "text": "Full-back Matthew Burke finished with a personal haul of 24 points to take his tour aggregate to 136.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 10, "end": 23, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Matthew Burke"}]}
{"id": "test-03129", "text": "RUGBY UNION - AUSTRALIA BEAT BARBARIANS 39-12.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 11, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "RUGBY UNION"}, {"start": 14, "end": 23, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "AUSTRALIA"}, {"start": 29, "end": 39, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "BARBARIANS"}]}
