{"id": "test-03172", "text": "CRICKET - JONES HITS CENTURY AS VICTORIA FIGHT BACK.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 10, "end": 15, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "JONES"}, {"start": 32, "end": 40, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "VICTORIA"}]}
{"id": "test-03173", "text": "HOBART, Australia 1996-12-07", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 6, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "HOBART"}, {"start": 8, "end": 17, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Australia"}]}
{"id": "test-03174", "text": "Former Australia test batsman Dean Jones hit an unbeaten 130 to lead Victoria's fightback in their Sheffield Shield match against Tasmania on Saturday.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 7, "end": 16, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Australia"}, {"start": 30, "end": 40, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Dean Jones"}, {"start": 69, "end": 77, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Victoria"}, {"start": 99, "end": 115, "ent_type": "MISC", "text": "Sheffield Shield"}, {"start": 130, "end": 138, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Tasmania"}]}
{"id": "test-03175", "text": "Replying to the home side's first innings 481 for eight declared, Victoria reached 220 for three at close of play on the second day of the four-day match at Hobart's Bellerive Oval.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 66, "end": 74, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Victoria"}, {"start": 157, "end": 163, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Hobart"}, {"start": 166, "end": 180, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Bellerive Oval"}]}
{"id": "test-03176", "text": "Jones became the fourth century-maker of the match, equalling the feats of Tasmanian trio David Boon, Shaun Young and Michael DiVenuto.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 5, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Jones"}, {"start": 75, "end": 84, "ent_type": "MISC", "text": "Tasmanian"}, {"start": 90, "end": 100, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "David Boon"}, {"start": 102, "end": 113, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Shaun Young"}, {"start": 118, "end": 134, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Michael DiVenuto"}]}
{"id": "test-03177", "text": "Jones, who took over as captain for the match in the absence of Australia test leg-spinner Shane Warne, added 195 runs for the third wicket with left-hander Laurie Harper.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 5, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Jones"}, {"start": 64, "end": 73, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Australia"}, {"start": 91, "end": 102, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Shane Warne"}, {"start": 157, "end": 170, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Laurie Harper"}]}
{"id": "test-03178", "text": "Harper was eventually dismissed for 77 after the pair joined forces with their side reeling on nine for two.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 6, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Harper"}]}
{"id": "test-03179", "text": "Earlier, former Australia test batsman David Boon scored 118 and all-rounder Shaun Young hit 113.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 16, "end": 25, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Australia"}, {"start": 39, "end": 49, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "David Boon"}, {"start": 77, "end": 88, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Shaun Young"}]}
{"id": "test-03180", "text": "The pair hammered 36 boundaries between them.", "gold_mentions": []}
{"id": "test-03181", "text": "Pace bowler Ian Harvey claimed three for 81 for Victoria.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 4, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Pace"}, {"start": 12, "end": 22, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Ian Harvey"}, {"start": 48, "end": 56, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Victoria"}]}
{"id": "test-03182", "text": "CRICKET - SHEFFIELD SHIELD SCORE.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 10, "end": 26, "ent_type": "MISC", "text": "SHEFFIELD SHIELD"}]}
{"id": "test-03183", "text": "HOBART, Australia 1996-12-07", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 6, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "HOBART"}, {"start": 8, "end": 17, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Australia"}]}
{"id": "test-03184", "text": "Close of play score on the second day of the four-day Sheffield Shield cricket match between Tasmania and Victoria at Bellerive Oval on Saturday:", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 54, "end": 70, "ent_type": "MISC", "text": "Sheffield Shield"}, {"start": 93, "end": 101, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Tasmania"}, {"start": 106, "end": 114, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Victoria"}, {"start": 118, "end": 132, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Bellerive Oval"}]}
{"id": "test-03185", "text": "Tasmania 481 for eight declared (Michael DiVenuto 119, David Boon 118, Shaun Young 113); Victoria 220 for three (Dean Jones 130 not out).", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 8, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Tasmania"}, {"start": 33, "end": 49, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Michael DiVenuto"}, {"start": 55, "end": 65, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "David Boon"}, {"start": 71, "end": 82, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Shaun Young"}, {"start": 89, "end": 97, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Victoria"}, {"start": 113, "end": 123, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Dean Jones"}]}
{"id": "test-03186", "text": "SOCCER - SOUTH KOREA MOVE CLOSE TO QUARTER-FINAL BERTH.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 9, "end": 20, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "SOUTH KOREA"}]}
{"id": "test-03187", "text": "ABU DHABI 1996-12-07", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 9, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "ABU DHABI"}]}
{"id": "test-03188", "text": "South Korea made virtually certain of an Asian Cup quarter-final spot with a 4-2 win over Indonesia in a Group A match on Saturday.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 11, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "South Korea"}, {"start": 41, "end": 50, "ent_type": "MISC", "text": "Asian Cup"}, {"start": 90, "end": 99, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Indonesia"}]}
{"id": "test-03189", "text": "After going four up in the first 55 minutes South Korea allowed Indonesia, newcomers to Asian Cup finals, back into the match, conceding two goals from rare counter attacks.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 44, "end": 55, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "South Korea"}, {"start": 64, "end": 73, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Indonesia"}, {"start": 88, "end": 97, "ent_type": "MISC", "text": "Asian Cup"}]}
{"id": "test-03190", "text": "Kim Do Hoon opened the scoring for South Korea in only the fifth minute, turning unmarked on the penalty spot to fire a shot into the top corner.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 11, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Kim Do Hoon"}, {"start": 35, "end": 46, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "South Korea"}]}
{"id": "test-03191", "text": "It looked like turning into a rout as Hwang Sun Hong rapidly added two more in the seventh and 15th minutes but although the Koreans continued to dominate they failed to add to the score before the interval.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 38, "end": 52, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Hwang Sun Hong"}, {"start": 125, "end": 132, "ent_type": "MISC", "text": "Koreans"}]}
{"id": "test-03192", "text": "But they started the second half where they had left off and it was not long before they went four up, Ko Jeong Woon heading in from a free kick in the 55th minute.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 103, "end": 116, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Ko Jeong Woon"}]}
{"id": "test-03193", "text": "The Koreans then appeared to relax, allowing the Indonesians to get back into the match.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 4, "end": 11, "ent_type": "MISC", "text": "Koreans"}, {"start": 49, "end": 60, "ent_type": "MISC", "text": "Indonesians"}]}
{"id": "test-03194", "text": "Ronny Wabia scored for Indonesia three minutes later direct from a a corner kick that Korean goalkeeper Kim Byung reached with one hand but failed to keep out.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 11, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Ronny Wabia"}, {"start": 23, "end": 32, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Indonesia"}, {"start": 86, "end": 92, "ent_type": "MISC", "text": "Korean"}, {"start": 104, "end": 113, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Kim Byung"}]}
{"id": "test-03195", "text": "With 65 minutes gone Indonesia's Widodo Putra, who scored a spectacular goal against Kuwait on Wednesday, was again on target, breaking through the Korean defence to beat the keeper with a low shot.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 21, "end": 30, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Indonesia"}, {"start": 33, "end": 45, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Widodo Putra"}, {"start": 85, "end": 91, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Kuwait"}, {"start": 148, "end": 154, "ent_type": "MISC", "text": "Korean"}]}
{"id": "test-03196", "text": "Indonesian keeper Hendro Kartiko produced a string of fine saves to prevent the Koreans increasing their lead.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 10, "ent_type": "MISC", "text": "Indonesian"}, {"start": 18, "end": 32, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Hendro Kartiko"}, {"start": 80, "end": 87, "ent_type": "MISC", "text": "Koreans"}]}
{"id": "test-03197", "text": "Teams:", "gold_mentions": []}
